about.description: Foolbox is a Python library that let's you easily run adversarial attacks against machine learning models like deep neural networks. It is built on top of EagerPy and works natively with models in PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX, and NumPy.
about.summary: Foolbox Native is an adversarial attacks library that works natively with PyTorch, TensorFlow and JAX

name: foolbox
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "foolbox" %}
{% set version = "3.0.2" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: 24ad770345ae700bf876ead8279c427e40bb426c9aaaa46ad8ff50e32ea43b7b

build:
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"
  noarch: python

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python
  run:
    - git
    - eagerpy >=0.27
    - gitpython >=3.0.7
    - numpy
    - python
    - scipy
    - setuptools
    - requests
    - typing-extensions >=3.7.4.1

test:
  imports:
    - foolbox
    - foolbox.attacks
    - foolbox.models
    - foolbox.zoo

about:
  home: https://foolbox.jonasrauber.de/
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE # PR here: https://github.com/bethgelab/foolbox/pull/551
  summary: "Foolbox Native is an adversarial attacks library that works natively with PyTorch, TensorFlow and JAX"
  description: 
    Foolbox is a Python library that let's you easily run adversarial attacks against machine learning models like
    deep neural networks. It is built on top of EagerPy and works natively with models in PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX, and NumPy.
  doc_url: https://foolbox.readthedocs.io/en/stable/
  dev_url: https://github.com/bethgelab/foolbox/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ndmaxar
    - oblute
    - rluria14
